Magic numbers are bad. You could make a case for using x different constants here, but having five return conditions with this much repetitive code is just bad style.

Bad:
<code>function toReadableSize($size) {
switch (true) {
case $size &lt; 1024:
return sprintf(__n('%d Byte', '%d Bytes', $size, true), $size);
case round($size / 1024) &lt; 1024: 				return sprintf(__('%d KB', true), $this-&gt;precision($size / 1024, 0));
case round($size / 1024 / 1024, 2) &lt; 1024: 				return sprintf(__('%.2f MB', true), $this-&gt;precision($size / 1024 / 1024, 2));
case round($size / 1024 / 1024 / 1024, 2) &lt; 1024: 				return sprintf(__('%.2f GB', true), $this-&gt;precision($size / 1024 / 1024 / 1024, 2));
default:
return sprintf(__('%.2f TB', true), $this-&gt;precision($size / 1024 / 1024 / 1024 / 1024, 2));
}
}
};</code>
